pageContext.claim: “We have it totally under control. It's one person coming in from China, and we have it under control. It's going to be just fine.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump was asked during an interview with CNBC whether he had any concerns about a pandemic after the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) had identified a case of coronavirus in Washington state. That was the first sign that the virus might eventually spread via community transmission, but Trump dismissed any concern. Within weeks, Washington state would become the center of the outbreak in the United States.
